article.description: — Mark Sears had a career-high 33 points as Ohio beat South Carolina Upstate 85-70 on Tuesday.
article.headline: Sears carries Ohio over South Carolina Upstate 85-70
article.linkText: Sears carries Ohio over South Carolina Upstate 85-70
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- — Mark Sears had a career-high 33 points as Ohio beat South Carolina Upstate 85-70 on Tuesday. Sears made all 10 of his foul shots. He added eight rebounds. Jason Carter had 12 points for Ohio (9-2), which won its fourth consecutive game. Ben Vander Plas added 12 points and seven rebounds. Ben Roderick had 11 points. Bryson Mozone had 18 points for the Spartans (3-9). Jordan Gainey added 14 points. Khydarius Smith had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
